				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Dolalin -- I completely agree with your analysis and sentiments regarding the state of casual gaming in Everquest.  I've been playing 6 months and have a level 40 character.  The problem goes beyond the Ch lvl 60 issues you mentioned.  Far too many of the Evequest Quests for nice or important items require camping spawns for multiple hours at a time as just one component of the quest.  This severely disadvantages the casual gamer who has a family and work, assuming the gamer wants to keep the family together and not be visiting his kids on weekends.<BR>
<BR>
Ghoulbane was a great quest for a nice item (one that is effective for many levels after earning it) that didn't involve a huge commitment of time in one location.  Unfortunately, those types of quests are rare and as one gains higher levels, become nonexistant.<BR>
<BR>
If that's the way EQ will be in the future, then I can easily see ending my subscription in several months and gravitating to something such as DAoC, where casual gaming isn't as heavily penalized.<BR>
