			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				   <BR>
  My 2 cp,<BR>
     I am a casual player, I work 9am~6pm. Almost all of my friends online who live locally in Taiwan work the same hours, most are casual like me. I bought EQ when SoV came out but only have about 29 days logged in total.<BR>
   Although it is true of some of the issues you laid out, such as camping and farming &quot;in general&quot;. But I totally disagree with you on your comment about Japanese and &quot;SE&quot; Asian guilds dominating the patch spawns and what not.<BR>
     1.) So far the regular patches are &quot;usually&quot; run at 3AM PST for around 4 hours(if u don't believe me go to the official site and check). Which roughly translates to 6pm~10pm HK,Tokyo,Taipei time. Exactly when people would play on this side of the world. For the casual player who works they have the same schedule as any other working stiff does in the rest of world. On weekdays we gotta turn in at a reasonable hour or we're gonna be late to work the next day. So how would we be spawn jumping when we're about to turn in?<BR>
For the &quot;uber&quot; players in the so-called &quot;uber&quot; Asian guilds which running to popular belief are the students or other who have no restrictions on their time and can play 24hr a day or such. Unfortunately, more often the case is students here have a heavier work load than working folks.(with tutors or study class after school which usually ends at 4:30 pm and don't get back home till 11pm, YES WE'RE NERDY, ALOT OF US WERE BROUGHT UP AS NERDS j/k). This is just a sort of explanation of why I find your assumption of Asian guilds being filled with hardcore players different from the facts.(not to mention the language barrier which puts off most people here, since they have plenty of other choices of games to spend time on where they can use their native language)<BR>
   2.)I would really look forward to your showing us exactly which &quot;uber&quot; asian guilds are hogging the spawns on which server? I'm sure as most people who have played EQ for a moderate amount of time know of the famous guilds such as &quot;Afterlife&quot;, &quot;Fires of Heaven&quot; etc as guilds who were the &quot;first&quot; of any server to do and do away with many uber mobs. I don't recall any of these guilds or even the guilds that are less well known cross-server but are just as uber(Vis Maior on my own Q~ server) as being Asian. Yes I'm sure they all have Asian members but I'd really LOVE to see you name ONE example of an all Asian guild dominating on ANY server. <BR>
I cannot speak for other servers, Although I know that the majority of Taiwan players play on Nameless and even from the players there I know the only way they can get a spawn is to have someone volunteer to just &quot;sit&quot; there and wait it out(by consequence have folks on their backs and generally have RL start to go downhill) and even then they really can't do anything if one of the other guilds(regardless of where the players play) get wind and tear into the mob when they show up with a large and ready raid party while the unlucky guy sitting there has to wait for everyone on his side of the dateline to wakeup. But for example on the Quellious server, Purple Demesnes(spelling off I know :p ), the now defunct Cyclones, Hero of Heroes are all Asian guilds but I'd like to see someone from Vis Maior come out and cry and say &quot;AWWWW we can't get into NToV cuz those Asian guilds jumped the spawn.&quot;<BR>
 <BR>
/rant off<BR>
<BR>
I have never ranted during my period of playing EQ. But I found that I couldn't stop myself from wasting half an hour(at work :P ). To set the facts a little closer to the truth.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
Fgviksar lvl 48 monk of the Third Rung<BR>
&lt;controllers of chaos, Q~ server&gt;<BR>
    
				</font>
